                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="legend_content" value="• Parent workflow: Scheduled → polls ServiceDesk for open tickets (status=open) → For Each → calls child workflow&#xa;• Child workflow: Request trigger → Classifier Agent → Parse → Message Agent → Parse → PATCH ServiceDesk → POST action → Response&#xa;• No Table Storage / watermark — ServiceDesk status column = the state machine (open → processed)&#xa;• No DLQ — child workflow failures visible in run history; retried via Logic Apps built-in retry policies&#xa;• Responses API: Single POST call per agent, synchronous response — no thread/run/poll loop needed&#xa;• Classifier-Agent uses File Search tool (Vector Store with HR policies + taxonomy)&#xa;• Message-Agent: instructions-only (no tools) — generates HR summary (EN) + employee message (ticket lang. + EN)&#xa;• ServiceDesk write-back: child workflow PATCH classification + POST action note after both agents complete" style="text;html=1;fontSize=10;fontStyle=0;fillColor=none;strokeColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#555555;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="245" y="950" width="740" height="130" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
